      blurb: "Same Zermatt → Grindelwald rail journey (~3h 35m). If the weather is mediocre or you just want a relaxed, sit-down day, swap Pfingstegg for the turquoise Lake Brienz cruise. Boat is 100% FREE on Swiss Travel Pass, the senior sits the whole way, and Iseltwald is the picture-perfect lakeside village (yes — the Crash Landing on You pier). Covered deck means it works in light rain too. Optional Belle-Epoque paddle steamer 'Lötschberg' with open upper deck if your day matches its schedule.",
